  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NonCallingBytecode

    public class GE
extends ComparisonNumericalBinOpBytecode
    A bytecode that checks if the one but last element of the stack is greater than or equal to its last element. It leaves on the stack the Boolean result of the comparison.

    ..., value1, value2 -> ..., value1 ≥ value2
    Author:
    Fausto Spoto

      • generateJavaBytecode

        public org.apache.bcel.generic.InstructionList generateJavaBytecode(JavaClassGenerator classGen)
        Generates the Java bytecode that leaves on the stack the Boolean value resulting from a ≥ comparison of two values. Namely, it generates the Java bytecode

        if_icmpge after
        iconst 0
        goto follow
        after: iconst 1
        follow: nop

        if ComparisonBinOpBytecode.type is int and

        fcmpl
        ifge after
        iconst 0
        goto follow
        after: iconst 1
        follow: nop

        if ComparisonBinOpBytecode.type is float. The fcmpl Java bytecode operates over two float values on top of the stack and produces an int value at their place, as it follows:

        ..., value1, value2 -> ..., 1 if value1 > value2
        ..., value1, value2 -> ..., 0 if value1 = value2
        ..., value1, value2 -> ..., -1 if value1 < value2
        Specified by:
        generateJavaBytecode in class NonBranchingBytecode
        Parameters:
        classGen - the Java class generator to be used for this generation
        Returns:
        the Java bytecode as above, depending on ComparisonBinOpBytecode.type
